        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()

            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

        <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }
              
            
        </script>

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()

            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

        <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }
              
            
        </script>

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

        <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }
              
            
        </script>

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }
              
            
        </script>

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()

        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }
              
            
        </script>

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()

            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()

            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }
              
            
        </script>

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

        <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>

        <script type="text/javascript">
        
        'use strict';
        
        $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        function ShowAlertMess(mess)
        {
          	var html = '<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><a class="close" data-dismiss="alert" href="#"></a>'+mess+'</div>';
            $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
        }    
        
        function getSearchData(JSONobject) {
          //console.log( JSONobject  );
          //JSONobject = ParseJson(JSONtext);
        
          var city = JSONobject.list;
          if( city.length == 0 ) {
            ShowAlertMess( 'Not found' );
            return;
          }
        
          var html = '';
        
          for(var i = 0; i <  JSONobject.list.length; i ++){
        
        
            var name = JSONobject.list[i].name +', '+JSONobject.list[i].sys.country;
        
            var temp = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp -273.15))/10 ;
            var tmin = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_min -273.15)) / 10;
            var tmax = Math.round(10*(JSONobject.list[i].main.temp_max -273.15)) / 10 ;
        
            var text = JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].description;
            var img =  "http://openweathermap.org/img/wn/" +JSONobject.list[i].weather[0].icon + "@2x.png";
            var flag = "http://openweathermap.org/images/flags/" +JSONobject.list[i].sys.country.toLowerCase()  + ".png";
            var gust = JSONobject.list[i].wind.speed;
            var pressure = JSONobject.list[i].main.pressure ;
            var cloud=JSONobject.list[i].clouds.all ; 
        
            
            var row = '<tr><td><img src="' + img + '" width="50" height="50"></td><td><b><a href="/city/' + JSONobject.list[i].id + '"> ' + name + '</a></b> <img src="' + flag + '" ><b><i> ' + text + '</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">' + temp + ' </span> temperature from '+ tmin + ' to ' + tmax + ' , wind ' + gust+ ' m/s. clouds ' + cloud + ' %, ' + pressure + ' hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + '&lon=' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + '">[' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat + ', ' + JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon + ']</a></p></td></tr>';
                    
            
           /* var column = `<td><img src="${img}"></td><td><b><a href="/city/${JSONobject.list[i].id}"> ${name}</a></b> <img src="${flag}"><b><i> ${text}</i></b><p><span class="badge badge-info">${temp}  </span> temperature from ${tmin} to ${tmax}, wind ${gust} m/s. clouds ${cloud}%, ${pressure} hpa</p><p>Geo coords <a href="/weathermap?zoom=12&lat=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}&lon=${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}">[${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lat}, ${JSONobject.list[i].coord.lon}]</a></p></td>`; 
            var row = `<tr>${column}</tr>`;
            */
            
            html = html + row;    
        
          }
        
           /* html=`<table class="table">${html}</table>`; */
           html='<table class="table">' + html + '</table>';
        
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html(html);
          //ShowInfoMess(html);
          $("#pbar").hide("fast");
        
        }
        
        function FindCity() {
         // $("#pbar").style.visibility = 'visible';
          $("#pbar").show("fast");
          $("#forecast_list_ul").html('');
          var param = document.getElementById('search_str').value;
          var jsonurl = "/data/2.5/find?callback=?&q="+param+ "&type=like&sort=population&cnt=30&appid=439d4b804bc8187953eb36d2a8c26a02";
          $.getJSON(jsonurl, getSearchData).error();
          return false; 
        }
        
        function GetURLParameter(sParam)
        {
            var sPageURL = window.location.search.substring(1);
            var sURLVariables = sPageURL.split('&');
            for (var i = 0; i < sURLVariables.length; i++)
            {
                var sParameterName = sURLVariables[i].split('=');
                if (sParameterName[0] == sParam)
                {
                    return sParameterName[1];
                }
            }
        }
        
        var q = GetURLParameter('q');
        if ( q ) {
        FindCity();
        }
              
            
        </script>

        <script>
            
            var bannerClosed = "owm_banner_android_closed"
            
            function getCookie(name) {
              const value = `; ${document.cookie}`;
              const parts = value.split(`; ${name}=`);
              if (parts.length === 2) return parts.pop().split(';').shift();
            }
            
            function setCookie (name, value) {
                var expires = new Date()
                expires.setTime(expires.getTime() + (5 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24))
                document.cookie = name + '=' + escape(value) + '; expires=' + expires.toGMTString() + '; path=/'
              }
              
            function bannerClose() {
                document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = "none";
                setCookie(bannerClosed, true)
            }
            
            document.onload = function(bannerClosed) {
               if ((document.cookie.indexOf() === -1)  && /Android/i.test(window.navigator.userAgent)) {
                   document.getElementById("banner_android").style.display = 'flex';
                } 
            }()
            
            
        </script>

        <div class="col-sm-12">
        
            <h3>Search engine is very flexible. How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
            <li> To make it more precise put the city's name, comma,  2-letter country code (ISO3166). You will get all proper cities in chosen country.
        <br>The order is important - the first is city name then comma then country. Example - London, GB or New York, US.</li>
            </ul>
